snippet: Pakistan had reached 131 for two before tea on day four of the first day-night test against Australia, still 359 runs behind their victory target, when rain stopped play at the Gabba on Sunday....
lead_paragraph: Pakistan had reached 131 for two before tea on day four of the first day-night test against Australia, still 359 runs behind their victory target, when rain stopped play at the Gabba on Sunday.

headline.main: Pakistan Reach 131-2 as Rain Stops Play Before Tea
